[capture](parameters) -> return_type {
    // function body
}
capture: variables from the surrounding scope you want to use inside.

parameters: arguments like a normal function.

return_type: usually deduced automatically (so you donâ€™t write it).

body: what the function does.
// example: when i want sort 2d int vecotr non decreasing order based on their starting value
sort(intervals.begin(), intervals.end(),
     [](const vector<int>& a, const vector<int>& b){
         return a[0] < b[0];
     });
